{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"be4744f0-5169-4c05-b8d4-1d3dac122f70","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (or `Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync` for async) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n}\n```\n\n**Why migrate?**\n\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if the exception is thrown *anywhere* in the test — even in the arrange step — masking bugs.\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the check to the exact call, and lets you inspect the exception:\n\n```csharp\nvar ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n    () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\nAssert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3ea3d204-01b7-4d77-b924-7bb5bc2352c5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":263,"requestId":"A042:2FE433:D67D35:FB5517:69FE8DE2"},"id":"72d92cfc-1f17-425b-8ad3-d6bfa8897bd9","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:29:12.354Z","parentId":"5c8521c3-e4ae-4046-83f3-62c9b3a1388b"}
